'Saint Louis County' (abbreviated 'St. Louis County') is a county located in the
U.S. state of Minnesota. As of the 2010 census, the population was 200,226. Its county seat is Duluth. It is the largest
county by total area in Minnesota, and the second largest in the United States
east of the Mississippi River; in land area alone, after Aroostook County,
Maine. Duluth News Tribune September 22, 2004, p. 2B. According to the U.S.
Census Bureau, Arostook County has a smaller overall area but a greater land
area. Major industries include pulpwood production and tourism. Surface
mining of high-grade iron-ore remains an important part of the economy of the
Iron Range. Parts of the Bois Forte and Fond du Lac Indian reservations are in
the county.
